  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) mandates\n\n3. Key Legal Principles\n- Criminalization of money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Civil penalties\n- Financial institution oversight\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Customer due diligence procedures\n- Internal control frameworks\n\n6. Penalty Structures\n- Criminal sanctions\n- Financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n7. Regulatory Agencies\n- Financial regulators\n- Criminal investigation departments\n- Treasury departments\n- Specialized anti-money laundering units\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
